@node Introduction "TRC User's Guide | Introduction"
@toc  Contents
@{u}@{b}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

The TRC program is a playing aid for Avalon Hill's classic board wargame, The
Russian Campaign.  The TRC program allows two players to conveniently play
The Russian Campaign by e-mail.  The features include:

     Fully computer based PBEM.  No map must be kept set up, no error prone
      recording of unit locations must be done.

     Simple, mouse based unit manipulation.

     Fast, compiled, OS friendly code.

     Respects font and resolution preferences.


@{b}Important:  This program is a play-aid only.  Ownership of the board
game is necessary for play.  There are no game rules in this distribution.@{ub}
The board game The Russian Campaign is published by Avalon Hill.  Contact
your usual wargame sources if you require a copy.

@endnode


@remark-----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node Requirements "TRC User's Guide | Introduction | System Requirements"
@toc  Contents
@{u}@{b}System Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

System requirements for the TRC program are modest.  A minimum is:

    68020
    WB2.04
    1MB Chip RAM
    1MB Fast RAM

However, a system capable of 640 x 400 resolution or better is recommended
as is WB3.x.  The resolution recommendation is so that the graphics are
proportioned correctly and to keep map scrolling to a minimum.  The WB3.x
recommendation is due to the bulk of the program testing being done with
WB3.1.


@endnode


