@node Installation "TRC User's Guide | Introduction | Installation"
@toc  Contents
@{u}@{b}Installation@{ub}@{uu}

The TRC program comes with an Installer script which can be run simply by
double clicking on the Install icon.

If for some reason you need to install TRC manually:

    copy the contents of the libs drawer to LIBS:
    copy everything else to whatever drawer you'd like, but maintain
     the directory structure of the distribution.


@endnode

@remark-----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node Start-up "TRC User's Guide | Introduction | Start-up"
@toc  Contents
@{u}@{b}Start-up@{ub}@{uu}

The program can be launched from either the Workbench or CLI.  If launched
from the CLI, the current directory must be the TRC program directory so it
can find the map file.

The TRC program runs on a custom screen, cloning the mode and resolution of
the default (usually Workbench) screen.

There are no tool-types or command line arguments.

The distribution contains a saved game file called AtStart.trc.  This file
contains the at start Russian and German forces for the standard campaign
game already deployed on the map in their appropriate military districts and
army groups.

@endnode

