@node Mouse "TRC User's Guide | Reference | Mouse Input"
@toc  Contents
@{u}@{b}Mouse Input@{ub}@{uu}

Most player activity is centred on manipulation of the units.  This section
defines mouse and key combinations for the various types of unit manipulation
which occurs during play.  The button and key combinations have been chosen
with the primary goal of serving the TRC program needs.  A secondary goal
has been to parallel typical Amiga convention where reasonable.

@{b}Task@{ub}                       @{b}Mouse@{ub}

Pick up a unit.            Click.

Pick up more units.        Shift Click.

Place held unit.           Click.

Cycle Stack                L-Alt Click.

Flip a unit.               L-Amiga Click


Note:  Unfortunately the choice to use the left modifier keys can conflict
with some Intuition shortcuts.  In particular the screen drag shortcut as
specified in the IControl prefs program defaults to L-Amiga and thus
conflicts with Flip Unit.  This shortcut must be turned off while playing
TRC.  (This author simply turned it off period since he never uses it).
Someday this issue will be addressed in a more elegant fashion.

@endnode


